    helpText: 'Partner work is a crucial component of many dance styles and requires different skills than solo technique, including communication, timing, and spatial awareness with another person. Practicing with multiple partners helps you adapt to different heights, movement styles, and experience levels while developing versatility in partner connection. This research phase helps you understand what type of partner work feels natural and what areas need focused development before committing to regular partner classes or social dancing events.'
